message.content:
1. GRFT gels were not associated with any significant changes to protein levels at any time point.
2. The comparison was made against a placebo.
3. The threshold for significance in protein level changes was an FDR less than 5%.
4. HEC-GRFT gel increased abundances of two common and beneficial microbial taxa after 24 hours.
5. The increase in microbial taxa abundance was statistically significant with a p-value less than 2E-09.

messages.content:
Statement: Compared to placebo, GRFT gels were not associated with any significant changes to protein levels at any time point (FDR < 5%), but increased abundances of two common and beneficial microbial taxa after 24 hours were observed in HEC-GRFT gel (p < 2E-09).
